# 📘 OOP (PBO) Assignment - Java

## 📌 Description
This project is part of an Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) course assignment. It demonstrates the implementation of a custom class (`SepedaMotor`) using constructors and methods, as well as basic CRUD concepts.

## 🏍️ Case Study
Motorcycle (SepedaMotor)

## 🎯 Features
- Default Constructor
- Parameterized Constructor
- Method (void) → display data
- Method (return) → tax calculation

## ⚙️ CRUD Concept
- Create → Object creation
- Read → Display object data
- Update → Setter method
- Delete → Handled by Java Garbage Collector

## ▶️ How to Run
1. Open project in NetBeans
2. Run `Main.java`
3. View output in console

## 🧪 Example Output
```

--- Object 1 ---
Motorcycle Details: Not Set General (0cc)

--- Object 2 ---
Motorcycle Details: Kawasaki KLX 150 (150cc)
Estimated Tax: Rp75000.0

```

